+# PW-D01: Playwright Runner And Project Bootstrap Contract
+
+## Status
+
+**Proposed.** This decision becomes accepted only after independent review of
+the exact pull-request head SHA and merge by Eddie or the Operator.
+
+## Governance And Scope
+
+| Field | Value |
+|---|---|
+| Work item | `slarti/backlog#254` (`PW-D01`) |
+| Frozen plan | `playwright-execution-plan-v1` |
+| Frozen plan approval | `yeraziael/slartis-backlog#83`, review `4757129666` |
+| Approved plan head | `d1379fbb065b0888e1615bce49205384b3f1a4ba` |
+| Architecture base | `ed54f1144f1df21af13c9a2a1fd5c685fa2a95ac` |
+| Execution mode | Sol high, architecture decision only |
+
+This document selects the immutable runner and Node project contract consumed
+by PW-I01. It does not create the project, install dependencies, edit CI, pull
+the image into a production runtime, execute a browser, or change any service.
+
+## Context
+
+The shared browser platform requires one local/CI execution contract with no
+host Node.js dependency, no persistent browser service, no mutable image tag,
+and no package-manager choice left to a low-cost implementation agent.
+
+The official Playwright image contains browser binaries and system libraries,
+but not the `@playwright/test` project dependency. The image version and project
+package version must match exactly or Playwright may not find the bundled
+browsers.
+
+The Gitea Actions runner and the Architecture workstation are linux/amd64. The
+Pi5 is not a browser runner and is outside this decision.
+
+## Decision Summary
+
+| Concern | Decision |
+|---|---|
+| Playwright release | `1.61.1` |
+| Image tag | `mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.61.1-noble` |
+| Multi-platform index digest | `sha256:5b8f294aff9041b7191c34a4bab3ac270157a28774d4b0660e9743297b697e48` |
+| Selected linux/amd64 manifest | `sha256:cf0daee9b994042e011bc29f20cdff1a9f682a039b43fcd738f7d8a9d3bcd9d6` |
+| Runtime image reference | `mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.61.1-noble@sha256:cf0daee9b994042e011bc29f20cdff1a9f682a039b43fcd738f7d8a9d3bcd9d6` |
+| Base OS | Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (Noble) |
+| Platform | `linux/amd64` |
+| Node.js | `24.17.0`, supplied by the pinned image |
+| npm | `11.13.0`, supplied by the pinned image |
+| Test package | `@playwright/test@1.61.1` exactly |
+| Required browser project | Chromium only |
+| Chromium binary | Chrome for Testing `149.0.7827.55`, revision `1228` |
+| Package manager | npm; no pnpm, Yarn, or host package manager |
+| Lock file | committed `tests/playwright/package-lock.json`, lockfile version 3 |
+| Project module mode | ECMAScript modules (`"type": "module"`) |
+| Local entry point | `make test-playwright-platform` |
+| CI entry point | `make test-playwright-platform` |
+| Make target command | `bash tests/playwright/runner/run.sh platform` |
+
+The platform-specific manifest digest, not the mutable tag and not only the
+multi-platform index digest, is the runtime identity. The human-readable tag is
+retained before `@sha256` so package/image version drift is visible in review.
+
+## Required PW-I01 Paths
+
+PW-I01 MUST use these exact paths:
+
+```text
+tests/playwright/
+├── package.json
+├── package-lock.json
+├── playwright.config.ts
+├── README.md
+└── runner/
+    └── run.sh
+
+tests/test_playwright_bootstrap.py
+```
+
+PW-I01 may add only the root `.gitignore` entries needed for:
+
+```text
+/test-results/playwright/
+/tests/playwright/node_modules/
+```
+
+CI registration remains manifest-first through the existing files named in
+PW-I01. Generated CI artifacts MUST NOT be edited by hand.
+
+## Node Project Contract
+
+`tests/playwright/package.json` MUST declare:
+
+- `private: true`;
+- `type: "module"`;
+- `packageManager: "npm@11.13.0"`;
+- exact engines `node: "24.17.0"` and `npm: "11.13.0"`;
+- exact dev dependency `@playwright/test: "1.61.1"` with no range prefix;
+- a `test:platform` script that runs the controlled platform suite through
+  `playwright.config.ts` and project `chromium`.
+
+The lock file MUST:
+
+- be generated with npm `11.13.0`;
+- use lockfile version 3;
+- contain no floating dependency declaration;
+- be installed with `npm ci`, never `npm install`, during runner execution.
+
+No separate `typescript` package is selected. Playwright's supported built-in
+TypeScript loading is sufficient for the initial configuration and tests.
+
+## Playwright Configuration Contract
+
+`tests/playwright/playwright.config.ts` MUST initially define exactly one
+browser project named `chromium` using Playwright's bundled Chromium. It MUST
+set `chromiumSandbox: false` explicitly; PW-I01 runs only controlled local
+content with no network and does not introduce the additional seccomp artifact
+required for a sandboxed `pwuser` configuration.
+
+PW-I01 MUST NOT enable Firefox, WebKit, videos, service-specific URLs,
+authentication, retries, or live Homelab tests. Later tickets own those
+concerns.
+
+The initial output root is `/results` inside the container and
+`$REPOSITORY_ROOT/test-results/playwright` on the host.
+
+## Runner Entry Contract
+
+`tests/playwright/runner/run.sh` is the only Docker invocation authority for
+local and CI execution. Make and Gitea Actions call the wrapper; they MUST NOT
+duplicate `docker run` arguments.
+
+The wrapper MUST:
+
+1. Resolve the repository root from its own path, not the caller's current
+   directory.
+2. Create the host results directory before starting Docker.
+3. invoke the exact image and `--platform linux/amd64`;
+4. use `docker run --rm --init` for dependency installation and
+   `docker run --rm --init --ipc=host` for browser execution;
+5. mount the repository read-only at `/workspace`;
+6. mount the results directory read-write at `/results`;
+7. set the working directory to `/workspace/tests/playwright`;
+8. create one uniquely named temporary Docker volume for
+   `/workspace/tests/playwright/node_modules` and remove it in an exit trap;
+9. run a dependency phase with that volume read-write, explicit Docker bridge
+   networking, no secrets, and only the locked npm install command;
+10. run the browser phase with `--network none` and the dependency volume
+    read-only;
+11. provide ephemeral writable tmpfs mounts for `/tmp` and `/root/.npm` in each
+    phase;
+12. run both phases with a read-only root filesystem, all Linux capabilities
+    dropped, and `no-new-privileges`;
+13. install the locked project with
+    `npm ci --ignore-scripts --no-audit --no-fund`;
+14. run only the selected package script with no network-fetched executable;
+15. preserve the child exit code unchanged until PW-I03 introduces the final
+    `0/1/2` result mapper;
+16. run the browser phase as the invoking host UID/GID so `/results` ownership
+    is correct without `chown` or an added capability;
+17. never mount the Docker socket, home directory, credential directory, SSH
+    directory, or any service runtime path.
+
+The dependency phase has registry access but no credentials, service variables,
+results mount, or browser execution:
+
+```bash
+docker run --rm --init \
+  --platform linux/amd64 \
+  --network bridge \
+  --read-only \
+  --cap-drop ALL \
+  --security-opt no-new-privileges \
+  --tmpfs /tmp:rw,nosuid,nodev,size=512m \
+  --tmpfs /root/.npm:rw,nosuid,nodev,size=128m \
+  --workdir /workspace/tests/playwright \
+  --mount type=bind,src="$REPOSITORY_ROOT",dst=/workspace,readonly \
+  --mount type=volume,src="$NODE_MODULES_VOLUME",dst=/workspace/tests/playwright/node_modules \
+  --env CI=true \
+  --env HOME=/tmp/pw-home \
+  --env npm_config_registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/ \
+  mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.61.1-noble@sha256:cf0daee9b994042e011bc29f20cdff1a9f682a039b43fcd738f7d8a9d3bcd9d6 \
+  /bin/bash -lc 'test "$(node --version)" = v24.17.0 && test "$(npm --version)" = 11.13.0 && npm ci --ignore-scripts --no-audit --no-fund'
+```
+
+The browser phase has no network and cannot modify installed dependencies:
+
+```bash
+docker run --rm --init --ipc=host \
+  --platform linux/amd64 \
+  --network none \
+  --read-only \
+  --cap-drop ALL \
+  --security-opt no-new-privileges \
+  --user "$HOST_UID:$HOST_GID" \
+  --tmpfs /tmp:rw,nosuid,nodev,size=512m \
+  --tmpfs /root/.npm:rw,nosuid,nodev,size=128m \
+  --workdir /workspace/tests/playwright \
+  --mount type=bind,src="$REPOSITORY_ROOT",dst=/workspace,readonly \
+  --mount type=volume,src="$NODE_MODULES_VOLUME",dst=/workspace/tests/playwright/node_modules,readonly \
+  --mount type=bind,src="$RESULTS_DIR",dst=/results \
+  --env CI=true \
+  --env HOME=/tmp/pw-home \
+  --env PLAYWRIGHT_RESULTS_DIR=/results \
+  mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.61.1-noble@sha256:cf0daee9b994042e011bc29f20cdff1a9f682a039b43fcd738f7d8a9d3bcd9d6 \
+  /bin/bash -lc 'mkdir -p "$HOME" && npm run test:platform'
+```
+
+The shell fragments are contract templates, not implementation in this decision
+artifact. PW-I01 owns safe array-based shell construction, invoking UID/GID
+capture, unique volume naming, and cleanup traps. The dependency volume MUST be
+removed after every pass, failure, signal, or prerequisite error.
+
+## Network Boundary
+
+PW-I01 platform/bootstrap browser tests MUST run with `--network none`; they use
+only controlled local content. This makes browser execution independent of DNS,
+TLS, Keycloak, services, and the Internet.
+
+The preceding dependency phase MAY reach only the explicitly configured package
+source `https://registry.npmjs.org/` to execute the lockfile-bound `npm ci`. It
+receives no runtime secret or service environment variable and does not launch a
+browser. Registry dependency integrities remain bound by `package-lock.json`.
+
+Service-network mode is not enabled by PW-I01. A later reviewed ticket MUST
+explicitly introduce its network argument and service/Keycloak target contract
+before a live service suite runs. Host networking, published ports, and Docker
+socket access remain forbidden.
+
+The dependency phase runs as image root but launches no browser and receives no
+secret. The browser phase runs as the invoking host UID/GID with Chromium's
+sandbox explicitly disabled. This decision compensates with controlled local
+content, network-none platform mode, an ephemeral container, read-only root and
+source mounts, dropped capabilities, no-new-privileges, no Docker socket, and
+no persistent browser state. Untrusted websites are outside the platform scope.
+
+## Local And CI Invocation
+
+Local operators and CI MUST use the same command from the repository root:
+
+```bash
+make test-playwright-platform
+```
+
+The generated Make target MUST invoke:
+
+```bash
+bash tests/playwright/runner/run.sh platform
+```
+
+No global Node.js, npm, Playwright, browser, or browser-system package is a host
+prerequisite. Docker and access to the pinned MCR image are the only runtime
+tool prerequisites.
+
+## Version And Upgrade Contract
+
+An upgrade MUST change the following in one reviewed PR:
+
+1. Playwright release/tag.
+2. Multi-platform index digest recorded for provenance.
+3. Selected linux/amd64 manifest digest used at runtime.
+4. Exact `@playwright/test` package version.
+5. Image-supplied Node/npm assertions if they changed.
+6. Chromium version/revision record.
+7. `package-lock.json`.
+8. Platform self-test evidence and all active service smoke evidence.
+
+The upgrade author MUST verify the tag and digests from MCR and the package
+version from the official NPM registry. A tag-only update is invalid.
+
+Rollback is one Git revert to the previous accepted decision/runner/package
+set. Image, package, browser, Node/npm assertions, and lock file MUST roll back
+together. No partial browser or package downgrade is allowed.
+
