+## Considered Alternatives
+
+### Mutable Image Tag
+
+Rejected. A version tag alone can be republished and does not satisfy PWR-001.
+
+### Multi-Platform Index Digest As Runtime Identity
+
+Rejected for execution. It is retained as provenance, but the linux/amd64
+manifest is selected directly so the runner cannot silently resolve another
+architecture.
+
+### Host-Installed Node And Browsers
+
+Rejected. Host versions would diverge between local and CI execution and would
+make browser/system dependencies persistent.
+
+### Custom Playwright Image
+
+Rejected for the initial platform. It would add image build, registry,
+provenance, patching, and release responsibilities before they are needed.
+
+### pnpm Or Yarn
+
+Rejected. The pinned official image already provides npm, the repository has no
+existing Node package-manager convention, and adding another bootstrap tool
+would increase moving parts without benefit for this single project.
+
+### Firefox And WebKit In The Initial Project
+
+Deferred. The binaries are present in the official image, but PWR-060 makes
+Chromium the required baseline and PWDEC-007 defers secondary browsers.
+
+### Persistent Dependency Or Browser Volume
+
+Rejected. It would retain state between runs and violate the ephemeral runner
+contract. Dependency and npm cache mounts are tmpfs for every invocation.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- Local and CI execution share one wrapper and one immutable runtime.
+- Every run pays the cost of an isolated dependency phase and `npm ci`;
+  reproducibility and clean state take priority over initial speed.
+- Platform browser execution runs without any network, service, or credential;
+  only the preceding secret-free dependency phase reaches the npm registry.
+- Live service networking remains explicitly blocked until a later reviewed
+  ticket introduces it.
+- Root is limited to the secret-free dependency phase; browser execution uses
+  the invoking UID/GID and the compensating controls in this decision.
+- Image/package upgrades are atomic and reviewable.
+
+## PW-I01 Handoff Gate
+
+PW-I01 may begin only after this decision is independently approved at its exact
+PR head SHA and merged. Its executor MUST implement this contract literally and
+MUST escalate rather than choose a different image, digest, Node/npm version,
+package manager, path, mount, command, browser project, or network mode.
